  "prompt": "What is the salary of various elected representatives in India?",
  "response": "As of my last knowledge update in October 2021, the salaries and allowances of elected representatives in India are defined by the government and are subject to periodic revisions. Here are the approximate salaries for various elected representatives:\n\n1. **Members of Parliament (MPs)**:\n   - Basic Salary: \u20b91,00,000 per month.\n   - Allowances: MPs receive additional allowances for office expenses, travel, and constituency work, which can significantly increase their total remuneration.\n\n2. **Members of Legislative Assembly (MLAs)**:\n   - Basic Salary: Varies by state, but typically around \u20b970,000 to \u20b91,00,000 per month, depending on the state.\n   - Allowances: MLAs receive additional allowances which may include constituency allowances, travel allowances, and more.\n\n3. **Chief Ministers (CMs)**:\n   - Salary: Varies by state; typically ranges from \u20b91,00,000 to \u20b92,00,000 per month.\n   - Allowances: Like other politicians, CMs receive various allowances.\n\n4. **State Governors**:\n   - Salary: Approximately \u20b93,50,000 per month.\n   - Benefits: Governors are provided with various facilities and benefits, including residence and staff.\n\n5. **Panchayati Raj Representatives (such as Sarpanch)**:\n   - Salary: Varies widely depending on the state and the specific position, but often quite modest. Sarpanchs may receive a nominal monthly salary, but they typically have some allowances for their duties.\n\nThe actual salaries and allowances can vary, and various states may have different rules in this regard. Additionally, these figures might have changed since my last update, so it is advisable to check with official government publications or reliable news sources for the most current information.",
